Tamara--

A couple of thoughts.  First, the reason why the Energy Division nixed
PG&E's advice filing had nothing to do with its proposal to price the
retained generation at the ISO ex post energy price, but rather with the
proposal contained therein to transfer the balances in its gen memo accounts
to its TCBA.  Thus, it is very possible that PG&E could turn around and
refile the advice letter, removing this element, and focusing solely on the
substitute pricing mechanism.  If they did that, we could protest at that
time.

The other option is that we could send a letter to the Commissioners,
advisors, and energy division stating our concern about the PX becoming a
dysfunctional market and not an adequate basis to develop the PX credit.



Jeanne      

